10/12/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The governments of BiH and Croatia plan to set up a joint commission to protect the Neretva River and the area where it flows into the Adriatic, said Croatian Environmental Minister Ivo Banac during a visit in Sarajevo on Wednesday (10 December).
He met with BiH Foreign Trade Minister Dragan Doko to discuss a project for integrated management of the Neretva and Trebisnjica rivers, with support from the World Bank.
(HINA - 10/12/03)
